"The look on the writing of a man who died 300 years ago fascinates me", says Rhodes with a serious face.
When I hold a letter in my hand, I feel a personal connection.
A Castle in England, a graphic novel, documents the lives of families who lived at Scotney Castle from the Middle Ages to the Edwardian period, each story illustrated by a different British artist - Isaac Lenkiewicz, Briony May Smith, William Exley, Becky Palmer and Isabel Greenberg.
However, it is not Rhodes' first book inspired by archives: he is also the author of Dead Men's Teeth and Other Stories (2014), a collection of British Library inspired documents - a project that was very emotional for him.
I was struck by a thumbprint on a letter written by a double agent in the 1970s who worked for the Jacobites, he said.
It's his fingerprint!
