When I smell the letter now, 300 years later, it's like I'm back in time.
How I love the archives!
For someone who is so fascinated by old papers, the support from the National Trust and Arts Council England and the possibility of spending almost four months at the castle is almost like a dream.
Rhodes spent time exploring the Victorian New Castle, browsing the archives and studying many treasures and curiosities, such as the head of a hyenas on the wall and bottles that were thrown down for centuries in a ditch.
He walked the plot and explored the ruins of the old castle, talking to the landlords, gardeners, and sometimes also to artists who worked on illustrations for his book.
He drank whiskey and wrote at night.
